01:29:33,161 --> 01:29:34,537
I'm finished.

1373
01:29:34,704 --> 01:29:38,207
Any second that phone's gonna ring
and Clarence McElheny is gonna tell me...

1374
01:29:38,375 --> 01:29:41,210
...Mr. Jensen wants me in his office
tomorrow morning...

1375
01:29:41,378 --> 01:29:44,838
...so he can personally chop my head off.

1376
01:29:45,507 --> 01:29:47,883
Four hours ago, I was the sun god at CCA.

1377
01:29:48,051 --> 01:29:52,137
Mr. Jensen's hand-picked golden boy,
the heir apparent.

1378
01:29:52,305 --> 01:29:56,892
Now, ha, ha, I'm a man without a corporation.

1379
01:29:57,978 --> 01:30:00,145
Let's get back to Howard Beale.

1380
01:30:01,481 --> 01:30:04,650
You're not seriously gonna pull Beale
off the air?

1381
01:30:08,947 --> 01:30:12,950
Mr. Jensen's unhappy with Howard Beale
and wants him discontinued.

1382
01:30:13,118 --> 01:30:15,494
But he may be unhappy,
but he isn't stupid enough...

1383
01:30:15,662 --> 01:30:18,539
...to withdraw the number-one show
on television out of pique.

1384
01:30:18,707 --> 01:30:21,584
Two billion dollars isn't pique!
That's the wrath of God!

1385
01:30:21,751 --> 01:30:24,086
And the wrath of God wants Howard Beale fired!

1386
01:30:24,254 --> 01:30:26,755
Every other network will grab him
the minute he walks.

1387
01:30:26,923 --> 01:30:29,633
He'll be back on the air for ABC
and we'll lose 20 points--

1388
01:30:29,801 --> 01:30:32,344
I'm gonna impale the son of a bitch
with a sharp stick!

1389
01:30:32,512 --> 01:30:35,180
- Forty million loss in revenues.
- I'll take out a contract.

1390
01:30:35,348 --> 01:30:38,642
- Let's not discount federal action...
- I'll hire professional killers.

1391
01:30:38,810 --> 01:30:43,981
No, I'll do it myself.
I'll strangle him with a sash cord!

1392
01:30:44,316 --> 01:30:47,484
--and a breach of the consent decree.
I don't think Jensen's gonna fire anybody.

1393
01:30:53,283 --> 01:30:54,700
Hackett.

1394
01:30:56,911 --> 01:31:00,372
Yes, Clarence.
I've already booked my flight.

1395
01:31:02,083 --> 01:31:04,418
Uh, well, can you give me
a little more time than that?

1396
01:31:04,586 --> 01:31:07,296
I've got the red-eye flight,
I won't be back in New York...

1397
01:31:07,464 --> 01:31:09,632
...till 6 tomorrow morning.

1398
01:31:11,593 --> 01:31:13,636
That'll be just fine.

1399
01:31:13,887 --> 01:31:15,554
I'll see you then.

1400
01:31:24,189 --> 01:31:27,483
Mr. Jensen wants to meet
Howard Beale personally.

1401
01:31:28,026 --> 01:31:31,779
He wants Mr. Beale in his office
at 10:00 tomorrow morning.

1402
01:31:38,286 --> 01:31:40,996
The final revelation is at hand.

1403
01:31:41,164 --> 01:31:45,250
I have seen the shattering fulgurations
of ultimate clarity.

1404
01:31:45,418 --> 01:31:50,255
The light is impending.
I bear witness to the light!

1405
01:32:11,069 --> 01:32:12,653
Good morning, Mr. Beale.

1406
01:32:12,821 --> 01:32:15,531
- They tell me you're a madman.
- Only desultorily.

1407
01:32:15,699 --> 01:32:18,033
- How are you now?
- I'm as mad as a hatter.

1408
01:32:18,201 --> 01:32:19,868
Who isn't?

1409
01:32:20,453 --> 01:32:22,621
I'm going to take you into our conference room.

1410
01:32:22,789 --> 01:32:26,125
Seems more seemly a setting
for what I have to say to you.

1411
01:32:27,460 --> 01:32:29,878
I started as a salesman, Mr. Beale.

1412
01:32:30,046 --> 01:32:32,923
I sold sewing machines and automobile parts...

1413
01:32:33,091 --> 01:32:36,009
...hairbrushes and electronic equipment.

1414
01:32:36,177 --> 01:32:38,512
They say I can sell anything.

1415
01:32:39,347 --> 01:32:42,599
I'd like to try to sell something to you.

1416
01:32:46,187 --> 01:32:49,815
Valhalla, Mr. Beale. Please, sit down.

1417
01:33:19,304 --> 01:33:24,099
You have meddled with the primal forces
of nature, Mr. Beale.

1418
01:33:24,267 --> 01:33:28,604
And I won't have it! Is that clear?

1419
01:33:28,897 --> 01:33:31,356
You think you've merely stopped a business deal.

1420
01:33:31,524 --> 01:33:33,066
That is not the case.

1421
01:33:33,234 --> 01:33:36,153
The Arabs have taken billions of dollars
out of this country...

1422
01:33:36,321 --> 01:33:38,197
...and now they must put it back!

1423
01:33:38,364 --> 01:33:43,535
It is ebb and flow, tidal gravity,
it is ecological balance.

1424
01:33:45,121 --> 01:33:46,872
You are an old man...

1425
01:33:47,040 --> 01:33:50,876
...who thinks in terms
of nations and peoples.

1426
01:33:51,044 --> 01:33:54,421
There are no nations, there are no peoples.
There are no Russians.

1427
01:33:54,589 --> 01:33:57,049
There are no Arabs.
There are no Third Worlds.

1428
01:33:57,217 --> 01:33:58,383
There is no West!

1429
01:33:58,551 --> 01:34:03,514
There is only one holistic system of systems.

1430
01:34:03,681 --> 01:34:05,891
One vast and immane...

1431
01:34:06,059 --> 01:34:08,894
...interwoven, interacting, multi-variate...

1432
01:34:09,062 --> 01:34:12,231
...multinational dominion of dollars.

1433
01:34:12,398 --> 01:34:15,526
Petrol dollars, electro-dollars,
multi-dollars.

1434
01:34:15,693 --> 01:34:21,448
Reichsmarks, rins, rubles, pounds and shekels.

1435
01:34:22,784 --> 01:34:27,246
It is the international system of currency
which determines...

1436
01:34:27,413 --> 01:34:30,791
...the totality of life on this planet.

1437
01:34:31,751 --> 01:34:36,255
That is the natural order of things today.

1438
01:34:37,382 --> 01:34:41,134
That is the atomic...

1439
01:34:41,302 --> 01:34:43,428
...and subatomic...

1440
01:34:43,596 --> 01:34:48,934
...and galactic structure
of things today.

1441
01:34:49,686 --> 01:34:51,770
And you have meddled...

1442
01:34:51,938 --> 01:34:56,483
...with the primal forces of nature!

1443
01:34:56,776 --> 01:35:02,281
And you will atone.

1444
01:35:02,907 --> 01:35:05,284
Am I getting it through to you, Mr. Beale?

1445
01:35:08,746 --> 01:35:13,292
You get up on your little 21-inch screen...

1446
01:35:14,002 --> 01:35:18,881
...and howl about America
and democracy.

1447
01:35:19,465 --> 01:35:23,802
There is no America.
There is no democracy.

1448
01:35:23,970 --> 01:35:29,474
There is only IBM and ITT and AT&T...

1449
01:35:29,642 --> 01:35:35,230
...and Dupont, Dow,
Union Carbide, and Exxon.

1450
01:35:35,398 --> 01:35:38,984
Those are the nations of the world today.

1451
01:35:39,360 --> 01:35:43,488
What do you think the Russians talk about
in their councils of state? Karl Marx?

1452
01:35:43,656 --> 01:35:45,991
They get out their linear programming charts...

1453
01:35:46,159 --> 01:35:48,660
...statistical decision theories,
minimax solutions...

1454
01:35:48,828 --> 01:35:52,289
...and compute price-cost probabilities
of transactions and investments...

1455
01:35:52,457 --> 01:35:53,498
...just like we do.

1456
01:35:54,000 --> 01:35:58,253
We no longer live in a world of nations
and ideologies, Mr. Beale.

1457
01:35:58,421 --> 01:36:03,091
The world is a college of corporations...

1458
01:36:03,760 --> 01:36:10,641
...inexorably determined
by the immutable bylaws of business.

1459
01:36:12,727 --> 01:36:15,687
The world is a business, Mr. Beale.

1460
01:36:17,607 --> 01:36:21,568
It has been since man crawled out of the slime.

1461
01:36:24,364 --> 01:36:29,284
And our children will live, Mr. Beale...

1462
01:36:30,662 --> 01:36:32,245
...to see that...

1463
01:36:34,540 --> 01:36:37,292
...perfect world...

1464
01:36:38,294 --> 01:36:41,505
...in which there's no war or famine...

1465
01:36:41,673 --> 01:36:45,008
...oppression or brutality.

1466
01:36:46,052 --> 01:36:50,013
One vast and ecumenical holding company...

1467
01:36:50,181 --> 01:36:54,476
...for whom all men will work
to serve a common profit...

1468
01:36:54,644 --> 01:36:58,897
...in which all men will hold
a share of stock...

1469
01:37:00,149 --> 01:37:03,068
...all necessities provided...

1470
01:37:03,778 --> 01:37:07,614
...all anxieties tranquillized...

1471
01:37:08,574 --> 01:37:12,494
...all boredom amused.

1472
01:37:18,459 --> 01:37:23,046
And I have chosen you, Mr. Beale...

1473
01:37:23,214 --> 01:37:25,716
...to preach this evangel.

1474
01:37:26,384 --> 01:37:28,010
Why me?

1475
01:37:29,262 --> 01:37:32,097
Because you're on television, dummy.

1476
01:37:32,974 --> 01:37:38,437
Sixty million people watch you every night
of the week, Monday through Friday.

1477
01:37:39,313 --> 01:37:41,606
I have seen the face of God.

1478
01:37:44,152 --> 01:37:46,737
You just might be right, Mr. Beale.

1479
01:37:48,281 --> 01:37:50,615
That evening, Howard Beale went on the air...

1480
01:37:50,783 --> 01:37:53,452
...to preach the corporate cosmology
of Arthur Jensen.

1481
01:37:53,619 --> 01:37:56,496
Last night I got up here and asked you people...

1482
01:37:56,664 --> 01:38:00,959
...to stand up and fight for your heritage,
and you did, and it was beautiful.

1483
01:38:01,127 --> 01:38:04,129
Six million telegrams were received
at the White House.

1484
01:38:04,297 --> 01:38:07,466
The Arab takeover of CCA has been stopped.

1485
01:38:07,633 --> 01:38:13,305
The people spoke, the people won.
It was a radiant eruption of democracy.

1486
01:38:13,473 --> 01:38:17,517
But I think that was it, fellas.

1487
01:38:17,685 --> 01:38:20,395
That sort of thing is not likely
to happen again.

1488
01:38:20,605 --> 01:38:23,565
Because at the bottom
of all our terrified souls...

1489
01:38:23,733 --> 01:38:26,777
...we know that democracy
is a dying giant...

1490
01:38:26,944 --> 01:38:31,740
...a sick, sick, dying, decaying,
political concept writhing in its final pain.

1491
01:38:31,908 --> 01:38:35,494
I don't mean that the United States
is finished as a world power.

1492
01:38:35,661 --> 01:38:37,829
The States is the richest and most powerful...

1493
01:38:37,997 --> 01:38:40,957
...the most advanced country,
light years ahead of any country.

1494
01:38:41,125 --> 01:38:43,835
I don't mean the communists
are gonna take over the world.

1495
01:38:44,003 --> 01:38:47,339
The communists are deader than we are.
What is finished...

1496
01:38:48,966 --> 01:38:52,427
...is the idea that this great country
is dedicated to the freedom...

1497
01:38:52,595 --> 01:38:56,306
...and flourishing of every individual in it.

1498
01:38:57,391 --> 01:39:00,352
It's the individual that's finished.

1499
01:39:00,770 --> 01:39:04,689
It's the single, solitary, human being
that's finished.

1500
01:39:05,566 --> 01:39:09,611
It's every single one of you out there
that's finished.

1501
01:39:10,154 --> 01:39:12,364
Because this is no longer...

1502
01:39:12,532 --> 01:39:16,243
...a nation of independent individuals.

1503
01:39:16,536 --> 01:39:19,329
It's a nation of some 200-odd million...

1504
01:39:19,497 --> 01:39:22,040
...transistorized, deodorized...

1505
01:39:22,208 --> 01:39:27,712
...whiter than white steel-belted bodies,
totally unnecessary as human beings...

1506
01:39:27,880 --> 01:39:31,258
...and as replaceable as piston rods.

1507
01:39:41,894 --> 01:39:45,105
Well, the time has come to say...

1508
01:39:45,273 --> 01:39:48,441
...is "dehumanization" such a bad word?

1509
01:39:48,818 --> 01:39:51,903
Whether it's good or bad, that's what is so.

1510
01:39:52,071 --> 01:39:57,242
The whole world is becoming humanoid,
creatures that look human but aren't.

1511
01:39:57,702 --> 01:39:59,077
The whole world, not just us.

1512
01:39:59,245 --> 01:40:03,415
We're just the most advanced country,
so we're getting there first.

1513
01:40:04,083 --> 01:40:09,045
The whole world's people are becoming
mass-produced, programmed...

1514
01:40:09,213 --> 01:40:10,964
...numbered insensate things.

1515
01:40:11,382 --> 01:40:13,425
It was a perfectly admissible argument...

1516
01:40:13,593 --> 01:40:16,178
...that Howard Beale advanced
in the days that followed.

1517
01:40:16,345 --> 01:40:19,222
It was, however, also a very depressing one.

1518
01:40:19,390 --> 01:40:22,726
Nobody particularly cared to hear
his life was utterly valueless.

1519
01:40:22,894 --> 01:40:24,728
By the end of the first week in June...

1520
01:40:24,896 --> 01:40:27,647
...the Howard Beale Show
dropped one point in the ratings...

1521
01:40:27,815 --> 01:40:32,444
...and its trend of shares dipped under 48
for the first time since last November.

1522
01:40:32,612 --> 01:40:36,615
You're his goddamn agent. I'm counting
on you to talk some sense into the lunatic.

1523
01:40:36,782 --> 01:40:40,285
Nobody wants to hear about
dying democracy and dehumanization.

1524
01:40:40,912 --> 01:40:41,995
I'm sorry I'm late.

1525
01:40:42,163 --> 01:40:44,372
We're starting to get rumbles from the agencies.

1526
01:40:44,540 --> 01:40:47,334
Another couple of weeks
and the sponsors will be bailing out!

1527
01:40:47,501 --> 01:40:50,629
This is a breach of contract.
This isn't the Howard Beale we signed.

1528
01:40:50,796 --> 01:40:55,091
Get him off that corporate universe kick,
or so help me, I'll pull it off the air!

1529
01:40:55,259 --> 01:40:58,386
I told him, Lou! I've been telling him
every day for a week!

1530
01:40:58,554 --> 01:41:01,640
I'm sick of telling him. Now you tell him!

1531
01:41:09,523 --> 01:41:10,899
Jesus Christ.

1532
01:41:14,403 --> 01:41:16,738
You could help me out
with Howard if you wanted to.

1533
01:41:16,906 --> 01:41:19,157
He listens to you. You're his best friend.

1534
01:41:19,325 --> 01:41:21,785
I'm tired of all this hysteria
about Howard Beale.

1535
01:41:21,953 --> 01:41:24,621
Every time you come
from seeing somebody in your family...

1536
01:41:24,789 --> 01:41:27,123
...you come back in one of these
middle-aged moods.

1537
01:41:27,291 --> 01:41:30,335
I'm tired of finding you on the telephone
every time I turn around.

1538
01:41:30,503 --> 01:41:33,338
I'm tired of being an accessory in your life.

1539
01:41:33,798 --> 01:41:36,341
And I'm tired of pretending to write
this dumb book...

1540
01:41:36,509 --> 01:41:39,678
...about my maverick days
in the great early years of television.

1541
01:41:39,845 --> 01:41:43,515
Every goddamned executive fired
from a network in the last 20 years...

1542
01:41:43,683 --> 01:41:47,686
...has written this dumb book
about the great early years of television.

1543
01:41:47,853 --> 01:41:51,147
And nobody wants a dumb, damn, goddamn book...

1544
01:41:51,315 --> 01:41:53,525
...about the early days of television.

1545
01:41:53,693 --> 01:41:56,736
Terrific, Max! Maybe you can start
a whole new career as an actor.

1546
01:41:56,904 --> 01:41:58,613
It's the truth.

1547
01:41:59,365 --> 01:42:04,119
After living with you for six months,
I'm turning into one of your scripts.

1548
01:42:04,912 --> 01:42:07,372
Well, this is not a script, Diana.

1549
01:42:07,707 --> 01:42:11,334
There's some real, actual life going on here.

1550
01:42:12,128 --> 01:42:15,714
I went to visit my wife today
because she's in a state of depression...

1551
01:42:15,923 --> 01:42:19,551
...so depressed that my daughter flew
all the way from Seattle to be with her.

1552
01:42:19,719 --> 01:42:21,720
And I feel lousy about that.

1553
01:42:21,887 --> 01:42:26,016
I feel lousy about the pain
that I've caused my wife and my kids.

1554
01:42:26,183 --> 01:42:28,101
I feel guilty and conscience-stricken...

1555
01:42:28,269 --> 01:42:30,895
...and all of those things
that you think sentimental...

1556
01:42:31,063 --> 01:42:35,025
...but which my generation
calls simple, human decency.

1557
01:42:39,030 --> 01:42:41,072
And I miss my home...

1558
01:42:41,782 --> 01:42:44,617
...because I'm beginning
to get scared shitless.

1559
01:42:44,785 --> 01:42:48,246
Because all of a sudden it's closer
to the end than it is to the beginning.

1560
01:42:48,414 --> 01:42:51,374
And death is suddenly
a perceptible thing to me...

1561
01:42:51,542 --> 01:42:54,044
...with definable features.

1562
01:42:58,090 --> 01:43:02,469
You're dealing with a man
that has primal doubts, Diana...

1563
01:43:02,803 --> 01:43:05,263
...and you've got to cope with it.

1564
01:43:05,848 --> 01:43:09,934
I'm not some guy discussing male
menopause on the Barbara Walters Show.

1565
01:43:10,603 --> 01:43:13,938
I'm the man that you presumably love.

1566
01:43:15,024 --> 01:43:17,942
I'm part of your life.

1567
01:43:18,110 --> 01:43:21,780
I live here. I'm real.

1568
01:43:22,948 --> 01:43:25,825
You can't switch to another station.

1569
01:43:33,292 --> 01:43:36,127
What exactly is it you want me to do?

1570
01:43:40,132 --> 01:43:43,176
I just want you to love me.

1571
01:43:44,428 --> 01:43:47,889
I just want you to love me,
primal doubts and all.

1572
01:43:50,226 --> 01:43:52,644
You understand that, don't you?

1573
01:43:57,650 --> 01:43:59,943
I don't know how to do that.

1574
01:44:11,664 --> 01:44:14,290
I'll be with you in a minute, Max.

1575
01:44:19,422 --> 01:44:20,922
By the first week in July...

1576
01:44:21,090 --> 01:44:23,216
...the Howard Beale Show
was down 11 points.

1577
01:44:23,384 --> 01:44:25,218
Hysteria swept through the network.

1578
01:44:25,386 --> 01:44:27,053
He's a plague. He's smallpox.

1579
01:44:27,221 --> 01:44:29,722
He's typhoid.
I don't wanna follow his goddamn show.

1580
01:44:29,890 --> 01:44:31,224
I want out of that 8:00 spot.

1581
01:44:31,392 --> 01:44:34,102
I've got enough troubles
without Howard Beale as a lead-in!

1582
01:44:34,270 --> 01:44:36,354
Scheduled me against Tony Orlando and Dawn.

1583
01:44:36,522 --> 01:44:39,774
NBC's got Little House on the Prairie.
ABC's got The Bionic Woman.

1584
01:44:39,942 --> 01:44:42,527
Do something! You gotta do something
about Howard Beale!

1585
01:44:42,695 --> 01:44:44,863
Get him off the air! Get him off!

1586
01:44:45,030 --> 01:44:46,656
Do something! Do anything!

1587
01:44:46,824 --> 01:44:48,825
We're trying to find a replacement for him!

1588
01:44:48,993 --> 01:44:51,035
I'm going to look at audition footage now!

1589
01:44:51,287 --> 01:44:54,747
And how when the sicks heal...

1590
01:44:54,915 --> 01:44:57,876
...man, I tell you I saw it!

1591
01:44:58,711 --> 01:45:03,798
It was heavy, baby.
I saw the earth quake.

1592
01:45:03,966 --> 01:45:07,719
And I saw the moon became like blood.

1593
01:45:07,887 --> 01:45:11,764
And every mountain and island
was moved from its place.

1594
01:45:11,932 --> 01:45:14,184
No, no, no. Damn it.

1595
01:45:14,351 --> 01:45:16,352
If we wanted hellfire we'd get Billy Graham!

1596
01:45:16,520 --> 01:45:19,898
Don't want faith healers, evangelists
or Oberammergau passion players!

1597
01:45:20,065 --> 01:45:23,109
What about that messiah
that ABC was supposed to have signed up...

1598
01:45:23,277 --> 01:45:25,945
- ...as our competition for next year?
- That's him.

1599
01:45:26,113 --> 01:45:30,408
- The bottomless pit is here.
- That's him?

1600
01:45:30,576 --> 01:45:32,452
His ass ending.

1601
01:45:32,620 --> 01:45:34,662
Jesus. Turn him off!

1602
01:45:35,789 --> 01:45:39,584
I've got three more,
but you've already seen the best ones.

1603
01:45:39,752 --> 01:45:42,587
