Howard Beale. Let's stop kidding ourselves.

1606
01:45:48,677 --> 01:45:51,513
Fully fledged messiahs don't come in bunches.

1607
01:45:51,680 --> 01:45:54,849
We either go with Howard Beale
or we go without him.

1608
01:45:55,017 --> 01:45:57,894
My reports say we'll do better without him.

1609
01:45:58,062 --> 01:46:00,939
It would be disaster to let this situation
go on another week.

1610
01:46:01,106 --> 01:46:03,733
By then, he'll be down 16 points...

1611
01:46:03,901 --> 01:46:07,278
...and the trend irreversible,
if it isn't already.

1612
01:46:08,489 --> 01:46:11,574
I think we should fire Howard.

1613
01:46:14,370 --> 01:46:20,124
Arthur Jensen has taken a strong personal
interest in the Howard Beale Show.

1614
01:46:22,127 --> 01:46:25,588
I'm having dinner with him tonight.
Let me have another crack at Jensen...

1615
01:46:25,756 --> 01:46:28,174
...and then let's meet in my office
at 10:00 tonight.

1616
01:46:28,342 --> 01:46:31,135
Diana, give me copies
of all your audience research reports.

1617
01:46:31,303 --> 01:46:35,431
I may need them for Jensen.
Is 10:00 convenient for everyone?

1618
01:47:07,464 --> 01:47:11,718
I think the time has come
to re-evaluate our relationship, Max.

1619
01:47:12,344 --> 01:47:14,012
So I see.

1620
01:47:15,598 --> 01:47:18,975
I don't like the way this script of ours
is turning out.

1621
01:47:19,143 --> 01:47:21,936
It's turning into a seedy little drama.

1622
01:47:22,104 --> 01:47:26,441
Middle-aged man leaves wife and family
for young heartless woman, goes to pot.

1623
01:47:26,609 --> 01:47:30,361
The Blue Angel with Marlene Dietrich
and Emil Jannings. I don't like it.

1624
01:47:30,529 --> 01:47:32,614
- So you're gonna cancel the show.
- Right.

1625
01:47:32,781 --> 01:47:34,699
Here, let me do that.

1626
01:47:36,285 --> 01:47:41,414
The simple fact is, Max,
that you're a family man.

1627
01:47:41,582 --> 01:47:45,335
You like a home and kids. That's beautiful.
I'm incapable of any such commitment.

1628
01:47:45,502 --> 01:47:48,421
All you'll get from me is
a couple months of intermittent sex...

1629
01:47:48,589 --> 01:47:51,966
...and recriminate and ugly little scenes
like the one we had last night.

1630
01:47:52,134 --> 01:47:55,720
I'm sorry for all those things
I said to you last night.

1631
01:47:55,888 --> 01:48:00,224
You're not the worst fuck I've ever had.
Believe me, I've had worse.

1632
01:48:00,726 --> 01:48:04,103
You don't puff or snorkle...

1633
01:48:04,271 --> 01:48:05,980
...and make death-like rattles.

1634
01:48:06,148 --> 01:48:08,941
As a matter of fact,
you're rather serene in the sack.

1635
01:48:10,277 --> 01:48:12,153
Why is it that a woman always thinks...

1636
01:48:12,321 --> 01:48:17,533
...that the most savage thing she can say
to a man is to impugn his cocksmanship?

1637
01:48:18,744 --> 01:48:22,080
Well, I'm sorry I impugned your cocksmanship.

1638
01:48:22,748 --> 01:48:26,542
I gave up comparing genitals
back in the schoolyard.

1639
01:48:36,178 --> 01:48:38,930
You're being docile as hell about this.

1640
01:48:39,973 --> 01:48:43,476
Oh, hell, Diana,
I knew it was over with us weeks ago.

1641
01:48:43,811 --> 01:48:46,479
Will you go back to your wife?

1642
01:48:48,482 --> 01:48:51,275
I'll give it a try,
but I don't think she'll jump at it.

1643
01:48:51,443 --> 01:48:53,695
But don't worry about me. I'll manage.

1644
01:48:53,862 --> 01:48:58,199
I always have, I always will.
I'm more concerned about you.

1645
01:48:59,034 --> 01:49:00,785
You're not the boozer type.

1646
01:49:00,953 --> 01:49:04,497
So I figure a year, maybe two,
before you crack up.

1647
01:49:04,665 --> 01:49:07,333
Or jump out of your 14th floor office window.

1648
01:49:07,501 --> 01:49:10,712
Stop selling, Max. I don't need you.

1649
01:49:22,099 --> 01:49:25,977
I don't want your pain. I don't want
your menopausal decay and death!

1650
01:49:26,145 --> 01:49:27,228
I don't need you, Max.

1651
01:49:27,396 --> 01:49:31,149
- Now get out of here!
- You need me! You need me badly.

1652
01:49:31,316 --> 01:49:34,110
Because I'm your last contact
with human reality.

1653
01:49:34,278 --> 01:49:36,279
I love you.

1654
01:49:36,447 --> 01:49:40,450
And that painful, decaying love
is the only thing between you...

1655
01:49:40,617 --> 01:49:43,536
...and the shrieking nothingness
you live the rest of the day.

1656
01:49:43,704 --> 01:49:45,329
Then don't leave me.

1657
01:49:48,459 --> 01:49:50,668
It's too late, Diana.

1658
01:49:51,795 --> 01:49:54,672
There's nothing left in you
that I can live with.

1659
01:49:57,384 --> 01:49:59,927
You're one of Howard's humanoids...

1660
01:50:00,095 --> 01:50:02,764
...and if I stay with you,
I'll be destroyed.

1661
01:50:03,432 --> 01:50:06,017
Like Howard Beale was destroyed.

1662
01:50:06,518 --> 01:50:09,145
Like Laureen Hobbs was destroyed.

1663
01:50:09,688 --> 01:50:13,524
Like everything that you
and the institution of television touch...

1664
01:50:13,692 --> 01:50:15,735
...is destroyed.

1665
01:50:21,533 --> 01:50:23,534
You're television incarnate, Diana.

1666
01:50:24,953 --> 01:50:30,333
Indifferent to suffering, insensitive to joy.

1667
01:50:31,627 --> 01:50:35,671
All of life is reduced
to the common rubble of banality.

1668
01:50:39,384 --> 01:50:42,303
War, murder, death...

1669
01:50:43,055 --> 01:50:46,224
...all the same to you
as bottles of beer.

1670
01:50:46,767 --> 01:50:51,437
And the daily business of life
is a corrupt comedy.

1671
01:50:52,606 --> 01:50:55,983
You even shatter the sensations
of time and space...

1672
01:50:56,151 --> 01:51:00,905
...into split seconds and instant replays.

1673
01:51:04,660 --> 01:51:06,369
You're madness, Diana.

1674
01:51:08,205 --> 01:51:10,540
Virulent madness.

1675
01:51:12,251 --> 01:51:15,378
And everything you touch dies with you.

1676
01:51:20,217 --> 01:51:22,009
But not me.

1677
01:51:22,970 --> 01:51:28,641
Not as long as I can feel pleasure and pain...

1678
01:51:32,437 --> 01:51:34,146
...and love.

1679
01:51:45,576 --> 01:51:46,659
And it's a happy ending.

1680
01:51:48,954 --> 01:51:52,623
Wayward husband comes to his senses...

1681
01:51:53,250 --> 01:51:54,834
...returns to his wife...

1682
01:51:55,043 --> 01:51:58,045
...with whom he's established
a long and sustaining love.

1683
01:51:59,256 --> 01:52:03,301
Heartless young woman left alone
in her arctic desolation.

1684
01:52:06,346 --> 01:52:08,639
Music up with a swell.

1685
01:52:11,560 --> 01:52:13,352
Final commercial.

1686
01:52:15,981 --> 01:52:19,567
And here are a few scenes from next week's show.

1687
01:52:31,496 --> 01:52:33,372
How did it go?

1688
01:52:50,015 --> 01:52:55,186
Mr. Jensen was unhappy at the idea
of taking Howard Beale off the air.

1689
01:52:56,438 --> 01:53:00,358
Mr. Jensen thinks Howard Beale
is bringing a very important message...

1690
01:53:00,525 --> 01:53:02,944
...to the American people.

1691
01:53:04,279 --> 01:53:07,865
So he wants Howard Beale on the air
and he wants him kept on.

1692
01:53:10,118 --> 01:53:13,120
Mr. Jensen feels we're too catastrophic
in our thinking.

1693
01:53:13,288 --> 01:53:17,458
I argued that television was a volatile
industry in which success and failure...

1694
01:53:17,626 --> 01:53:20,211
...were determined week by week.

1695
01:53:20,879 --> 01:53:24,382
Mr. Jensen said he did not like
volatile industries and suggested...

1696
01:53:24,549 --> 01:53:28,052
...with a certain sinister silkiness...

1697
01:53:28,929 --> 01:53:32,556
...that volatility in business
usually reflected bad management.

1698
01:53:33,558 --> 01:53:36,811
He didn't care if Howard Beale
was the number-one show or the 50th.

1699
01:53:36,979 --> 01:53:39,438
He didn't really care
if the Beale Show lost money.

1700
01:53:40,649 --> 01:53:45,111
He wants Howard Beale on the air
and he wants him kept on.

1701
01:53:45,821 --> 01:53:50,491
I would describe his position on this
as inflexible.

1702
01:53:51,243 --> 01:53:53,619
Where does that put us, Diana?

1703
01:53:54,496 --> 01:53:58,416
That puts us in the shithouse,
that's where that puts us.

1704
01:54:01,044 --> 01:54:03,879
- Do you want me to go through this?
- Yes.

1705
01:54:04,965 --> 01:54:09,260
The Beale Show Q score's down to 33.

1706
01:54:09,928 --> 01:54:13,389
Most of this loss occurred in the child
and teen and 18-34 categories...

1707
01:54:13,557 --> 01:54:16,809
...which were our key core markets.

1708
01:54:17,019 --> 01:54:20,146
And as the AR department's carefully
considered judgment and mine...

1709
01:54:20,313 --> 01:54:23,691
...that if we get rid of Beale,
we should maintain a respectable share...

1710
01:54:23,859 --> 01:54:26,736
...in the high 20s, possibly 30,
with a comparable Q level.

1711
01:54:26,903 --> 01:54:29,447
The other segments of the show,
Sibyl the Soothsayer...

1712
01:54:29,614 --> 01:54:33,784
...Jim Webbing, the Vox Populi,
have all developed their own audiences.

1713
01:54:33,952 --> 01:54:36,120
Our AR reports show that it is Howard Beale...

1714
01:54:36,288 --> 01:54:39,123
